VisuallyHidden.description: Renders an element that is visually only to screen readers

children.description: Content that will be only available for a screen reader

Tooltip.description: Tooltips display a label that was omitted when hovering the element. They shouldn't be essential for users to complete tasks.

gutter.description: Distance (in px) from the trigger reference @default 2

Toast.description: Toasts can appear at any time to provide instant feedback on actions. They are usually temporary, but can also require the user to dismiss.

onDismiss.description: Callback to be called when the toast is dismissed

duration.description: How long the toast should be visible for in milliseconds @default 5000

ToastStack.description: Toasts can appear at any time to provide instant feedback on actions. They are usually temporary, but can also require the user to dismiss.

TimeInput.description: A Time Input is a field for a single time value.

Textarea.description: Text Area is a field for text values that can take up more than one line in a form, such as descriptions or comments.

optional.description: Whether the textarea is optional or not

resizable.description: Whether the textarea is resizable or not @default true

Tag.description: Tags differentiate items through a read-only text value in a colored bg. They can be secondary or primary, given their relevance to the main job.

Table.description: Table lists items vertically and can include actions for each row. The columns display property values for users to scan, sort, and compare.

columnWidths.description: Array of column widths When using the Table component @default [] When using the SimpleTable component @default [repeat(${columns.length}, var(--sl-table-default-column-width))]

asChild.description: If true, the Table component will be rendered as a child of the Compose component @default false

stickyHeader.description: If true, the header will be sticky @default false

stickyColumn.description: If true, the first column will be sticky @default false

TableSortIndicator.description: Component that indicates if a column is sortable and its current sort direction

sorted.description: Indicates if column is currently sorted, and in witch order @default null

dimOnHover.description: Indicates that the row dims while hovered @default true

Tab.description: Tabs are used to create up to five views inside a page. Use for related content that is not comparable, when a unified view is not necessary.

TabPanel.description: Tabs are used to create up to five views inside a page. Use for related content that is not comparable, when a unified view is not necessary.

tabId.description: The id of the tab that controls this panel. By default, this value will be inferred based on the order of the tabs and the panels.

TabList.description: Tabs are used to create up to five views inside a page. Use for related content that is not comparable, when a unified view is not necessary.

horizontal.description: Switches the layout to horizontal @default false

fluid.description: Grows the width of items to match the parent @default false

Spinner.description: Spinner informs that a specific element in the page is loading or a task is in progress. Use only for request that take over 1s and less than 5s.

description.description: Specify a description that would be used to best describe the loading state @default 'loading'

size.description: Increase or decrease the size of the shape @default 16

Skeleton.description: Skeletons compose a low-fidelity representation of content that will load. They appear when the entire page is loading and take up to 5s.

Select.description: Select opens a dropdown with between five and seven values for users to choose one. Use Radios for less items or a Combobox for more items.

SelectValue.description: Renders the value of the select

hideOnClick.description: Whether to hide the select when this item is clicked. By default, it's true when the value prop is also provided. @default true

Search.description: Search is a text input that users can type to narrow down a Collection. Use Filters if values can be classified in predefined options.

loading.description: Whether component is loading or not @default false

onClear.description: Callback when the input is cleared @default undefined

messages.description: Object containing all messages to be displayed in the search input

placeholder.description: @deprecated You must use the messages property to override the placeholder label.

RangeCalendar.description: Allow users to select a date range

Radio.description: Radio inputs allow users to select one option from a list. It should be used inside a RadioGroup component.

RadioGroup.description: A group of Radios includes five options at most and only one can be selected at a time. Options can be listed horizontally or vertically.

error.description: Whether the radio group is in an error state

horizontal.description: Whether the radio group is horizontal or vertical @default false

Popover.description: Popover containers allow merchants to access and interact with more information of an item through an overlay.

Pagination.description: Pagination handles navigation inside a Collection. It displays the number of items, filtered or not, and allow users to navigate between pages.

onPageChange.description: Function called whenever the pagination actions are triggered and the page changes. @param page The new page number reference @param type The type of the action that was triggered

loading.description: Whether the pagination is loading or not. @default false

Page.description: The Page structure helps users to easily identify where they are, view content essential to the main job, and perform related actions.

Modal.description: Modal displays content related to a minor job within a page's main job. It demands complete attention and blocks interactions outside the overlay.

onClose.description: Callback fired when the backdrop or close button is clicked.

open.description: Whether the modal is open or not @default false

portal.description: Whether to render the modal inside a portal or not @default true

narrow.description: Decrease the space token in top and bottom padding. @default false

Menu.description: Menus summarize actions in a dropdown. They can include actions that are rarely used, complementary, or repeated for each item in a Collection.

MenuItem.description: Option within a menu popover box

LinkBox.description: A container that acts as a link. It allows text selection and stop its children event propagation.

Link.description: Links represent navigation inside a page or between pages, including to pages outside the Admin. They exist within or directly after a text.

optional.description: Whether the input linked to this label is optional @default false

Input.description: An Input is a field for short text values. It can include masks and character restrictions, such as accepting only numbers.

error.description: Whether there is an error @default false

disabled.description: Whether is disabled or not @default false

IconButton.description: Icon Buttons represent minor actions in a flow. It includes a label only for accessibility that is not visible, so the icon must be recognizable by itself.

loading.description: Disable the button and show a spinner. @default false

asChild.description: Merge button props with immediate child. @default false

label.description: Icon button label. Needed for accessibility.

Heading.description: Heading is used to define levels of typography

GridCell.description: Optional cell of a grid layout ://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/Grid

asChild.description: Children composition @default false @example <Flex asChild> <button> A flex button </button> </Flex>

Filter.description: Filters represent criteria that users can choose to narrow down a Collection. They can include single or multiple selection.

FilterTrigger.description: Triggers the Filter Popover box, also displays the Filter applied value

horizontal.description: Switches the layout to horizontal @default false

fluid.description: Grows the width of items to match the parent @default false

FilterClear.description: Action that clears both Filter value and UI Select value

FilterApply.description: Action that applies the Filter value, and closes the popover

FieldCharCounter.description: Count chars of a field that contains a input or textarea that has a max-length

EmptyState.description: An Empty State represents the state of a container, such as when there are no items to display or when the user isn't allowed to access items.

size.description: Indicates size of empty state area @default 'medium'

Divider.description: Creates distinction between sections in containers with constrained space or rows in a table.

DateRangePicker.description: A Date Range Picker is a field for date period values that may include time. The date can be typed or selected in a Calendar.

DatePicker.description: A Date Picker is a field for single date values that may include time. The date can be typed or selected with the help of a Calendar.

DateField.description: A list of date-segments used as base for date-picker and date-range-picker

Content.description: Content containers allow merchants to easily scan information to understand its hierarchy and rhythm. @playground

narrow.description: Decrease the space token in top and bottom padding. @default false

Container.description: Wraps Content component to support Container Queries

ConfirmationModal.description: Confirmation Modals appear after users attempt to trigger an action with an effect that is irreversible or hard to reverse, such as deleting items. [open, setOpen] = useState(false) const handleClose = () => { setOpen(false) } <Button onClick={() => setOpen((open) => !open)}> Open confirmation modal </Button> <ConfirmationModal open={open} onClose={handleClose} onConfirm={handleClose} onCancel={handleClose} > <Text variant="body">Hello world</Text> </ConfirmationModal>

onClose.description: Callback fired when the backdrop or close button is clicked.

onConfirm.description: Callback fired when the ok button is clicked.

onCancel.description: Callback fired when the cancel button is clicked.

open.description: Whether the modal is open or not. @default false

disabled.description: Whether the confirm actions is disabled. @default false

critical.description: Whether the confirm actions is critical. @default false

locale.description: The BCP47 language code for the locale. @link https://www.ietf.org/rfc/bcp/bcp47.txt @default en-US

messages.description: Object containing all messages to be displayed internally in the modal. They include "title", "ok" and "cancel".

props.description: Props to merge with element props

ref.description: Ref to merge with element ref

Compose.description: Composes immediate child with its props and child own props. Used to implement Shoreline composition Button({ asChild, ...props }){ const Composition = asChild ? Compose : 'button' return <Composition {...props} /> }

composeElement.description: Clone element merging its props and refs with passed props and refs. element: React.ReactNode = ... const props = {} cosnt ref = useRef() composeElement({ element, props, ref, })

props.description: Props to merge with element props

ref.description: Ref to merge with element ref

Composable.description: Defines a composable child inside of a Compose component Button({ asChild, children, ...props }){ const Composition = asChild ? Compose : 'button' return ( <Composition {...props}> Prefix <Composable>{children}</Composable> </Composition> ) }

render.description: Render function. Use it to wrap the root with containers

ComboboxPopover.description: Renders a popover for the combobox

ComboboxList.description: Renders a list for the combobox

ComboboxItem.description: Renders an item for the combobox

Collection.description: Collection combines a list of items with controls for the view. The list can be a Table and the controls can be a Search, Filters, and Pagination.

CollectionView.description: A collection view is a component that renders a collection based on its status

status.description: Represents the status of a collection and indicates what should be rendered @default 'ready'

onlyImmediateChild.description: if true only immediate children will bubble the event if false the immediate children and their children will bubble the event @default false

Checkbox.description: A single Checkbox represents binary choices, such as accepting terms and conditions or activating and deactivating notifications.

CheckboxGroup.description: A group of Checkboxes includes five independent choices at most. Each option is binary and they can be listed horizontally or vertically.

error.description: Whether the checkbox group is in an error state

horizontal.description: Whether the checkbox group is horizontal or vertical @default false

Calendar.description: Allow users to select a date

Button.description: Buttons with labels represent the most important actions that users frequently trigger. They can vary in prominence and can include an icon.

loading.description: Disable the button and show a spinner. @default false

asChild.description: Merge button props with immediate child. @default false

Bleed.description: Allows the content to bleed into the external container

Alert.description: Alerts call attention to a semantic message and load alongside the rest of the page content. They can optionally be dismissed upon user action.

variant.description: Variants of the alert, one of: informational, success, critical, warning. @default 'informational'

onDismiss.description: Callback fired when the alert is dismissed.

AccessibleIcon.description: Makes icons accessible by adding a label. It can be used with Shoreline icons or other svg.
